"},"id":"a3doW3GwihBT","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781866897493,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":10,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"0b460f74-de6d-4af3-a165-cd6bf5d4a336"},"execution_count":4,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["['age_years',\n"," 'gender',\n"," 'ssc_percentage',\n"," 'hsc_percentage',\n"," 'degree_percentage',\n"," 'degree_specialization',\n"," 'technical_score',\n"," 'aptitude_score',\n"," 'communication_score',\n"," 'skills_match_percentage',\n"," 'certifications_count',\n"," 'internship_experience',\n"," 'years_of_experience',\n"," 'career_switch_willingness',\n"," 'relevant_experience',\n"," 'previous_ctc_lpa',\n"," 'expected_ctc_lpa',\n"," 'company_tier',\n"," 'job_role_match',\n"," 'competition_level',\n"," 'bond_requirement',\n"," 'notice_period_days',\n"," 'layoff_history',\n"," 'employment_gap_months',\n"," 'relocation_willingness',\n"," 'status']"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":4}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 1: Job Acceptance Distribution\n","plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))\n","\n","ax = sns.countplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title('Distribution of Job Acceptance Status')\n","plt.xlabel('Job Acceptance Status')\n","plt.ylabel('Number of Candidates')\n","\n","for container in ax.containers:\n","    ax.bar_label(container)\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"WCs31aNPi95v","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781866955534,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":453,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"bd0f31b6-165e-492e-f71c-c62215f5d3bf"},"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 700x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["status_counts = df['status'].value_counts()\n","\n","print(status_counts)\n","\n","print(\"\\nAcceptance Percentage\")\n","print((status_counts / len(df) * 100).round(2))"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"__3gIWnojIVI","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781866991280,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":54,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"2e2d6875-ede0-4e90-9aa1-f3f109448980"},"execution_count":6,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["status\n","Not Placed    34950\n","Placed        15174\n","Name: count, dtype: int64\n","\n","Acceptance Percentage\n","status\n","Not Placed    69.73\n","Placed        30.27\n","Name: count, dtype: float64\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 2 – Target Variable Distribution\n","plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))\n","\n","sns.countplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Distribution of Job Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Candidates\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"FxrejTEljs4g","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867148283,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":591,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"d19691be-49b7-4380-d4ac-391ef574bdd9"},"execution_count":7,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 3 – Pie Chart of Placement Status\n","status_counts = df['status'].value_counts()\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))\n","\n","plt.pie(\n","    status_counts,\n","    labels=status_counts.index,\n","    autopct='%1.1f%%',\n","    startangle=90,\n","    colors=['skyblue','lightgreen']\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Placement Percentage\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":521},"id":"h0vAJdJvj1Ik","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867181178,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":150,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"0e7f9734-d1a9-4b36-cc8d-9defbf29ed43"},"execution_count":8,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Approximately 69.73% of candidates were not placed, while 30.27% were successfully placed. This indicates that the dataset is moderately imbalanced, with non-placement cases occurring more frequently than placement cases. During model evaluation, metrics such as Precision, Recall, F1-score, and ROC-AUC should be considered in addition to overall accuracy."],"metadata":{"id":"sMI2vydSj9DS"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 4 – Age Distribution by Placement Status\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='age_years',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Age Distribution by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Age (Years)\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":453},"id":"Kazydqvsj-NN","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867244101,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":317,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"ffe38356-7fd4-421b-8cc4-579818b6777a"},"execution_count":9,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The box plot shows that the age distributions of placed and not placed candidates are very similar. The median age of placed candidates is approximately 27 years, while the median age of not placed candidates is approximately 28 years. The interquartile ranges also overlap considerably, indicating that age alone is not a strong factor influencing job placement. No significant outliers are observed.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Median age (Placed): ~27 years\n","Median age (Not Placed): ~28 years\n","Similar spread for both groups\n","No notable outliers\n","Age alone does not appear to strongly influence placement."],"metadata":{"id":"ZNmCEL87mFtQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#5.Age Distribution (Histogram + KDE)\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.histplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='age_years',\n","    bins=20,\n","    kde=True,\n","    color='steelblue'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Distribution of Candidate Age\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Age (Years)\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Frequency\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":442},"id":"vtyRGajdk0wH","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867495439,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":631,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"83ea9046-f35c-4618-8e93-28d4d0bb5f75"},"execution_count":10,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The age distribution of candidates ranges from 21 to 34 years, with most candidates falling within this range. The histogram indicates that the dataset contains candidates from different age groups without any extreme concentration in a particular age. The distribution appears relatively uniform, suggesting that the dataset includes a balanced representation of young professionals and recent graduates."],"metadata":{"id":"0M_jc-6Vl8O2"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#6. Gender Distribution\n","plt.figure(figsize=(6,5))\n","\n","sns.countplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='gender',\n","    palette='pastel'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Gender Distribution\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Gender\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Count\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"gGhPXlHllQFJ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867555049,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":292,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"5cd510ff-2d3a-4730-865b-5056b273d18f"},"execution_count":11,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 600x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The gender distribution is nearly balanced, with male and female candidates represented in almost equal proportions. A balanced gender distribution reduces the possibility of gender bias in the dataset and allows machine learning models to learn from both groups fairly.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Nearly 50% Male\n","Nearly 50% Female\n","Well-balanced dataset"],"metadata":{"id":"JfP9_xaImQqw"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#7. Gender vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))\n","\n","sns.countplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='gender',\n","    hue='status',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Placement Status by Gender\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Gender\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Count\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"LfWySCRIlV50","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867576729,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":646,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"3f2ed868-be7e-4b06-8fe9-8b20fa0b3d9d"},"execution_count":12,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 700x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The placement status comparison across gender shows a similar pattern for both male and female candidates. In both groups, the number of candidates who were not placed is higher than those who were placed, reflecting the overall class distribution of the dataset. There is no obvious visual evidence that gender has a substantial impact on placement outcomes.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Similar placement trends for males and females.\n","More \"Not Placed\" than \"Placed\" for both genders.\n","Gender does not appear to be a dominant predictor of placement."],"metadata":{"id":"BGFTKAyFmY-d"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 8 – SSC Percentage vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='ssc_percentage',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"SSC Percentage by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"SSC Percentage\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":453},"id":"YyHOwpVJmZze","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867924353,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":520,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"3805b053-9685-4eda-d95d-aad4821b01e7"},"execution_count":13,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The SSC percentage distribution for placed and not placed candidates is highly similar. Both groups have a median SSC score of approximately 70%, with comparable interquartile ranges and overall spread. Although a few high-scoring candidates (above 90%) appear as outliers in both groups, there is no significant difference between the two categories. This suggests that SSC percentage alone is not a strong indicator of placement status in the dataset.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Median ≈ 70%\n","Similar variability for both groups\n","Several high-score outliers (>90%)\n","SSC percentage alone is not a strong predictor"],"metadata":{"id":"ubTSWfpknMMU"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 9 – HSC Percentage vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='hsc_percentage',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"HSC Percentage by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"HSC Percentage\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":453},"id":"kz-dckwVmwe9","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867955156,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":327,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"99d764ab-eeb3-4ef1-ce6b-6c1e371a03ef"},"execution_count":14,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The HSC percentage distributions for placed and not placed candidates exhibit nearly identical characteristics. Both groups have a median score of approximately 72%, with similar interquartile ranges and comparable score distributions. A few lower and higher outliers are observed, but there is no noticeable separation between the placement categories. Therefore, HSC percentage does not appear to have a strong independent influence on placement outcomes.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Median ≈ 72%\n","Similar distribution\n","Low-score and high-score outliers exist\n","No clear relationship with placement"],"metadata":{"id":"xHi2j-WUnRKv"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Visualization 10 – Degree Percentage vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='degree_percentage',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Degree Percentage by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Degree Percentage\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":453},"id":"ywbujwT7m4Of","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781867983146,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":542,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"b8e97b45-014c-4a94-c2bf-fec216730083"},"execution_count":15,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The degree percentage distribution is also very similar for both placed and not placed candidates. The median degree score is approximately 74% in both groups, and the spread of values overlaps considerably. While a few extreme observations are present, the overall distributions suggest that degree percentage alone does not significantly distinguish placed candidates from those who were not placed.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Median ≈ 74%\n","Nearly identical distributions\n","Similar variability\n","Weak standalone relationship with placement"],"metadata":{"id":"X5TakNEjnU6t"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#11. Technical Score by Placement Status\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='technical_score',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Technical Score by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Technical Score\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":448},"id":"OJ4GkEa3nV8V","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868179506,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":264,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"5d3d9b21-1f37-4839-eebe-7a6304fea20f"},"execution_count":16,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The technical score distribution shows a clear difference between placed and not placed candidates. Placed candidates have a noticeably higher median technical score (approximately 74–75) compared to not placed candidates (approximately 64–65). The interquartile range of the placed group is also shifted toward higher scores, indicating that candidates with stronger technical skills are more likely to secure placements. This suggests that technical score is an important predictor of placement status.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Placed candidates have a higher median technical score.\n","Most placed candidates score above 70.\n","Not placed candidates generally have lower technical scores.\n","Technical score appears to be a strong predictor of placement."],"metadata":{"id":"DxTeUs_LoXiQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#12. Aptitude Score by Placement Status\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='aptitude_score',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Aptitude Score by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Aptitude Score\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":448},"id":"TjJdZQ9Mnz1_","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868226074,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":624,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"2187f98f-a8db-4910-b96e-3cdc7f782aa2"},"execution_count":17,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The aptitude score distributions for placed and not placed candidates are relatively similar, although the placed group has a slightly higher median score. The large overlap between the two distributions indicates that aptitude score alone does not strongly distinguish placement outcomes. However, when combined with other features, aptitude score may still contribute to the predictive performance of machine learning models.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Slightly higher median for placed candidates.\n","Large overlap between both groups.\n","Weak individual relationship with placement."],"metadata":{"id":"jVm4_OXSoacu"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#13. Communication Score by Placement Status\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='communication_score',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Communication Score by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Communication Score\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":448},"id":"WvIkMeFln7ak","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868255050,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":488,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"989370dd-617a-4d29-ee4b-22070c65766f"},"execution_count":18,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","The communication score distributions show a modest difference between placed and not placed candidates. Placed candidates have a slightly higher median communication score, suggesting that stronger communication skills may improve employability. However, the substantial overlap between the two groups indicates that communication score alone is not sufficient to determine placement status.\n","\n","Key Findings\n","Slightly higher communication scores for placed candidates.\n","Considerable overlap between groups.\n","Moderate influence on placement."],"metadata":{"id":"u3_GyV6Hoboq"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#14. Internship Experience vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))\n","\n","sns.countplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='internship_experience',\n","    hue='status',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Placement Status by Internship Experience\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Internship Experience\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Candidates\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"eBilMRHzoeMp","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868557517,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":498,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"656f6229-0950-451b-f5fd-9a82e0127326"},"execution_count":19,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 700x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation:\n","The candidates with Internship got placed with better % when compared to the candidate with No internship experience."],"metadata":{"id":"v8gVDofJp0Uv"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#15. Relevant Experience vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(7,5))\n","\n","sns.countplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='relevant_experience',\n","    hue='status',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Placement Status by Relevant Experience\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Relevant Experience\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Candidates\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":487},"id":"MQj8trTIpNUH","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868591772,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":442,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"f24f0d37-db3e-452b-d1f7-8d70b66e861d"},"execution_count":20,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 700x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation:\n","Relevant experience plays a huge role as the majority of the placed candidates had relevant experience"],"metadata":{"id":"9ThfaA-8qELT"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#16. Years of Experience vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='years_of_experience',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Years of Experience by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Years of Experience\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":459},"id":"qgaPmY0epTlQ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868619985,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":59,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"403e456d-213a-416c-f7db-0cea9d61e380"},"execution_count":21,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation:\n","The placed candidates had a median of 2 years of experience than Not placed which had 1 year of experience. This shows experience has a role in placement status."],"metadata":{"id":"S4lzJbbrqPV1"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#17. Certifications Count vs Placement\n","plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n","\n","sns.boxplot(\n","    data=df,\n","    x='status',\n","    y='certifications_count',\n","    palette='Set2'\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Certifications Count by Placement Status\")\n","plt.xlabel(\"Placement Status\")\n","plt.ylabel(\"Number of Certifications\")\n","\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":459},"id":"sVk9hlBYpeQg","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781868662463,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":550,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"bf4a18a6-82e5-4f3d-fe41-528335bbbb15"},"execution_count":22,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 800x500 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#18 company_tier\n","sns.countplot(x='company_tier', hue='status', data=df)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":467},"id":"DDlt4BG9rUT5","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781869145061,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":582,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"f19930d4-4988-489e-8737-41671e5912dc"},"execution_count":27,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["<Axes: xlabel='company_tier', ylabel='count'>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":27},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation\n","\n","Candidates from higher-tier companies may exhibit higher selection rates.\n","Indicates prior work environment quality."],"metadata":{"id":"jpeMkcYkrbiI"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#19 expected_ctc_lpa\n","sns.histplot(df['expected_ctc_lpa'], kde=True)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":467},"id":"M3DjQGGDsesq","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781869453259,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":710,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"60e7d022-1cc9-45c8-c0e6-b5254d253ae9"},"execution_count":33,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["<Axes: xlabel='expected_ctc_lpa', ylabel='Count'>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":33},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["sns.boxplot(x='status', y='expected_ctc_lpa', data=df)"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":466},"id":"H_kDlh_LsjdY","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781869462540,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":278,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"c6d138f5-115f-4167-9985-8c4bb1c24d00"},"execution_count":34,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["<Axes: xlabel='status', ylabel='expected_ctc_lpa'>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":34},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Interpretation:\n","Expected CTC also played a slight role in the placement status as you could see the final placed candidates median had expected ctc ~6 LPA and not placed is at ~7 LPA."],"metadata":{"id":"MeGpBvTLsqGQ"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#Correlation Heatmap\n","heatmap_df = df.copy()\n","\n","heatmap_df['status'] = heatmap_df['status'].map({\n","    'Not Placed': 0,\n","    'Placed': 1\n","})\n","\n","plt.figure(figsize=(12,8))\n","\n","sns.heatmap(\n","    heatmap_df.corr(numeric_only=True),\n","    annot=True,\n","    cmap='coolwarm',\n","    fmt=\".2f\"\n",")\n","\n","plt.title(\"Correlation Heatmap\")\n","plt.show()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":526},"id":"Lr43nykosDtt","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781869358096,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":9965,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"24b91351-f3b6-4cd1-f418-ffb94629a438"},"execution_count":32,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x800 with 2 Axes>"],"image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["The exploratory data analysis revealed meaningful relationships between candidate attributes and hiring outcomes.Variables such as technical_score, skill_match_percentage, and years_of_experience showed a stronger association with the selection status while categorical features such as internship experience and relocation willingness demonstrated noticeable differences in selection rates"],"metadata":{"id":"s0m3ePeutKgE"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#ENCODING\n","df.select_dtypes(include='object').columns.tolist()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"sPoXb4BRtuCB","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781870017286,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":73,"user":{"displayName":"Ajith Balaji R","userId":"09038294931466871982"}},"outputId":"b4ecfd3b-6d3d-495f-c35e-b9d38a87a65c"},"execution_count":35,"outputs":[{"ou